---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';

const WORKSHOP_TITLE = 'Practical Generative AI Workshops | Auston Horras';
const WORKSHOP_DESCRIPTION =
	'Practical generative AI workshops for teams that want a clear understanding of where AI helps, where it fails, and how to use it inside real workflows.';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={WORKSHOP_TITLE} description={WORKSHOP_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<div class="page-shell">
			<header class="main-nav">
				<nav class="container nav-inner" aria-label="Primary">
					<a href="/" class="brand">austontatious.dev</a>
					<div class="nav-links nav-links-primary">
						<a href="/">Home</a>
						<a href="/workshops/" aria-current="page">Workshops</a>
						<a href="/Mimir">Mímir</a>
						<a href="https://github.com/austontatious" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">GitHub</a>
						<a href="mailto:auston.horras@gmail.com">Contact</a>
					</div>
				</nav>
			</header>

			<main class="workshop-main">
				<section class="section workshop-hero">
					<div class="container section-inner">
						<p class="eyebrow">Workshop Offering</p>
						<h1>Practical Generative AI Workshops</h1>
						<p class="lead workshop-lead">For teams that want to understand how AI actually fits into real work.</p>
						<p class="workshop-intro">
							These workshops are designed for organizations that have moved past novelty and want a clearer practical understanding of generative AI: what it can do well, where it breaks, how to work with it effectively, and how to think about implementation without getting lost in hype.
						</p>
						<div class="workshop-hero-actions">
							<a class="button button-primary" href="mailto:auston.horras@gmail.com?subject=Workshop%20Inquiry">Talk about a workshop</a>
							<a class="button button-secondary" href="#workshop-delivery">Delivery formats</a>
						</div>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section class="section">
					<div class="container section-inner workshop-content">
						<article class="workshop-panel">
							<h2>Not an “AI trends” talk</h2>
							<p>
								I am less interested in spectacle than in usefulness. The goal is not to impress a room for an hour. The goal is to leave people with a clearer mental model of AI, better judgment about where it fits, and practical ways to use it inside real workflows.
							</p>
						</article>

						<article class="workshop-panel">
							<h2>Built from implementation reality</h2>
							<p>
								This perspective comes from building agent systems, memory infrastructure, and applied tooling directly. The workshop content is designed to translate that implementation reality into decisions teams can use immediately.
							</p>
						</article>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section id="workshop-delivery" class="section">
					<div class="container section-inner workshop-content">
						<article class="workshop-panel">
							<h2>Delivery formats</h2>
							<ul>
								<li>Executive briefing</li>
								<li>2-4 hour interactive workshop</li>
								<li>Remote or on-site delivery</li>
								<li>Adaptable for technical, operational, or cross-functional audiences</li>
							</ul>
						</article>

						<article class="workshop-panel">
							<h2>What participants leave with</h2>
							<ul>
								<li>A clearer mental model of what AI systems actually do</li>
								<li>Practical prompting and review patterns that improve output quality</li>
								<li>A better sense of where AI helps, fails, and needs guardrails</li>
								<li>Concrete workflow habits teams can start using immediately</li>
							</ul>
						</article>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section class="section">
					<div class="container section-inner">
						<article class="workshop-panel">
							<h2>Example modules</h2>
							<ul>
								<li>How generative AI actually works in practice</li>
								<li>Using AI as a teammate instead of a search bar</li>
								<li>Prompting, review, and decision quality</li>
								<li>Failure modes, hallucinations, and false confidence</li>
								<li>Workflow design and human-in-the-loop systems</li>
								<li>What leaders should understand before buying or deploying AI tools</li>
							</ul>
						</article>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section class="section">
					<div class="container section-inner">
						<div class="workshop-cta">
							<h2>Interested in bringing this to your team?</h2>
							<p>
								If your team is trying to get past vague AI enthusiasm and into real understanding, I would be glad to talk.
							</p>
							<div class="cta-actions">
								<a class="button button-primary" href="mailto:auston.horras@gmail.com?subject=Workshop%20Inquiry">Start the conversation</a>
								<a class="button button-secondary" href="mailto:auston.horras@gmail.com">Contact by email</a>
								<a class="button button-secondary" href="/Mimir">Explore Mímir</a>
							</div>
							<a class="back-link workshop-back-link" href="/">Back to home</a>
						</div>
					</div>
				</section>
			</main>

			<footer class="site-footer">
				<div class="container footer-inner">
					<p>Calm systems for clear outcomes.</p>
					<div class="footer-links">
						<a href="mailto:auston.horras@gmail.com">Contact</a>
						<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/auston-horras-17022614/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>
						<a href="https://github.com/austontatious" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">GitHub</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</footer>
		</div>
	</body>
</html>
